
@startuml
' Define classes
class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: int
  -length: int (in seconds)
  -genre: String
  -artist: Artist
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -websiteURL: String
}

class User {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class BusinessUser {
  +vatNumber: String
  -- User
}

class RegularUser {
  -- User
}

class Single {
  -title: String
  -year: int
  -length: int (in seconds)
  -genre: String
  -artist: Artist
}

class Hit {
  -title: String
  -year: int
  -length: int (in seconds)
  -genre: String
  -artist: Artist
}

class Album {
  -title: String
  -trackList: List<Hit>
}

class Purchase {
  -song: Song
  -user: RegularUser
  -date: Date
}

class AlbumSuggestion {
  -album: Album
  -user: RegularUser
  -date: Date
}

' Relationships

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo
Artist "1" -- "*" Song : hasSongs
User <|-- BusinessUser
User <|-- RegularUser
BusinessUser "1" -- "*" Single : uploads
RegularUser "1" -- "*" Single : buys
RegularUser "1" -- "*" Album : creates
RegularUser "1" -- "*" AlbumSuggestion : suggests
Single "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo
Hit "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo
Album "1" -- "*" Hit : contains
@enduml

### Notes:
- `Song` and `Hit` are similar, but `Hit` is part of an `Album`, while `Single` is directly purchased by regular users.
- `Artist` is uniquely identified by name.
- A combination of `song` and `artist` must be unique.
- `BusinessUser` can only upload `Single`s.
- `RegularUser` can buy `Single`s and create `Album`s.
- `AlbumSuggestion` represents a suggestion made by a `RegularUser` to other users based on purchasing behavior.

